dataIdInfo.idAbs: Wildlife Management Units boundaries are created by using easily defined features on the ground such as roads and rivers to allow the public to easily determine which WMU they are in.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Boundaries used to manage and regulate harvests of wildlife populations according to specific area in Pennsylvania's.Wildlife Management Units (WMUs) are designed to manage all game, except elk, waterfowl and other migratory game birds.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Pennsylvania Game Commission, Bureau of Wildlife Management.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: WMUs are based on land use/habitat; human density; public/private land ownership; recognizable physical features, such as major roads and rivers; and land use practices, such as agriculture, timber, and development.
